{
  "text": "Off-loading is an etiologic therapy of neuropathic diabetic foot ulcers. When correctly applied, it has been proven not only to interrupt the pathogenic chain that produces the ulceration but also to induce modifications in the histology of the ulcer, shifting it from a chronic inflammatory state to a much more evolutive condition [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "40232439",
    "[CITATION_2]": "14037813"
